The following file contains info regarding the .py files present in the repository. 

# environments.py: 

It contains the classes for each environment type, using M_tot as the total mass = m1 + m2 in the formalism. 

# environments-m1.py:

It contains the classes for each environment type, using an approximated M_tot = m1 in the formalism. 

# handy_functions.py:

It contains the functions to perform the calculations for the dephasing and the time to coalescence, as well as other stuff (like the frqeuency grid and the 1yr-to-merge related frequency). 
